content: Worked well on my phone with no freezes. Controls are a bit close, resulting in a restart rather than an undo multiple times, but that was a relatively minor nuisance that was greatly overlooked by the ability to play this game again. Glad to see it on android. My only real complaint is that there aren't more levels.
Thank you so much for porting this to Android. Great job!

This is my all time favorite windows 95 game to play, the puzzle of hitting targets by solving the problem of obstruction and placing the rock on target by shoving them with the bulldozer ... sometimes it takes a while to figure out the placement or even the solution of how to tuck away and move the rock favorably to suit the field of play ... I like it cause I must think and process where I am going and shortest movement without getting trapped ... The controls are too small and too close together, which is the probable reason why handling the bulldozer is next to impossible. The drag option is a bad idea to boot. I'm using a Samsung galaxy duo s. The game itself is ingenious,  exactly like the original one. You should get rid of the empty spaces on each level, thereby freeing space for larger controls. And for crying out loud, place the restart button far, far, far away from the undo button. That having been said, it's only a buck, so buy it.
